Its a shootout,your Sundance im Cassidy" "With nothing tried their can be nothing lost" "You told me i was always right; Only confession i'll ever write" "My one fear is wasting all my time" "you always say your right, im always always wrong. Whats the point in another song?" "Ever had a question you didnt wanna ask? Ever get an answer you wish could be left in the past" "Got no answers but im so fucking sure about who i am, no i dont know anymore" "Ive come to find after much tribulation my worst enemy is me" "Catch me in a lie, please force me into change, otherwise i wont fucking change. Push me, fucking shove me" "time and time and time and time again, i begin, then i quit" "i wanna be that guy who walks with a sudden look in his eye" "i wanna get paid doing something i like, i want someone to tell me what im doing is right" "Nail myself down. Elaborations dead" "Things cant change ill always be, indecisive, see?"

I loaded 52(i counted) of my cd's onto my iTunes this past week...but for the past few days all have been listening to is Keasbey Nights.

"Keasbey Nights"(for those of you who dont know, and if you didnt know this, then your probably someone i hate...excluding gothy) is Catch22's first cd, and it was written entirely (lyrics, horn lines, everything) By TOM fucking KALNOKY who is a big inspiration to me and some of my friends...he is just an absolutley amazing musician. 

so anyway, he wrote this entire cd when he was a junior/senior in highschool, and it is highly proclaimed as one of the best SKA albums ever (the best ever according to TAANG is Turn the Radio Off by RBF, and i dont think anyone could deny that)

getting best ska album ever is like the biggest compliment ever. and he did it in his highschool days.

amazing.
